    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The inverse is XOR!</p>\n\n<p>If you have:</p>\n\n<pre><code>c = a^b;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>You can get <code>a</code> or <code>b</code> back if you have the other value available:</p>\n\n<pre><code>a = c^b; // or b^c (order is not important)\nb = c^a; // or a^c\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>For example if <code>a = 5</code>, <code>b = 3</code> (and thus <code>c = 6</code> as you mentioned) you get:</p>\n\n<pre><code>b=0011 (3)            a=0101 (5)\nc=0110 (6) XOR   or   c=0110 (6) XOR\n----------            ----------\na=0101 (5)            b=0011 (3)\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
