    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The inverse of XOR is XOR itself. For example if you take this operation :</p>\n<pre><code>3 ^ 4 = 7\n</code></pre>\n<p>The following statements are true :</p>\n<pre><code>4 ^ 7 = 3\n\n3 ^ 7 = 4\n</code></pre>\n<p>Hopefully, this helps.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 23565699,
      "reputation" : 59,
      "user_id" : 17606457,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9206c372b3bebc57fd142e5cf76017dd?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "aryan183",
